# Arcade Jam

*Note: there* will *be rambling. Caution is advised ;)*

## Theme is Loopholes

## Idea \#1: “Loop holes”

- “Loop holes”? Sorta like *Life is Strange*/*Minit*, where you need to escape a time loop of sorts but can take items or something  
  - ***Corrupting the storyline?***  
- Wider story game/visual novel maybe? Harder, but would be more impactful. Sorta like that one game where you need to do the puzzles that dantdm did and was made on construct *(There is no game)*  
- Loophole is an *ambiguity in a law exploited for an advantage.* “E.g. One ticket per email”, but you can have a thousand emails and it’s still allowed within the rules  
- Perhaps you need to exploit loopholes to get money/gain status/whatever? Sorta like Brain It Out

## Idea \#2: “Loophole Lawyers”

- AI game: Find loophole in laws to win your case  
- Other lawyers are AIs  
- Not super keen on this idea tbh

## Prior art(-ish)

- *There Is No Game:* a game where apparently there is no game, but you click the title’s letters to make them fall off etc. to progress the game. Sort of a loophole I guess?  
- *Brain It Out:* A simple puzzle game for mobile. You need to solve puzzles by unconventional means.  
  ![][image1]  
- *Minit:* You have one minute to escape. Not really loophole related, but could be related to loop holes?  
- *Life is Strange:* Rewinding time, *while keeping items and knowledge* you gleaned from conversations with other characters.

## Game loop

- Two minute loop. Your job is to get status (maybe become a ceo/prime minister/president? idk) or escape (not sure which one yet)  
- You can get information from other characters *and they won’t remember you gave it to them after loop restart*.  
- Perhaps you can blackmail other characters? Or create friendships to gain their trust?  
- ***You can keep items,*** but each item has a weight and holding too many items will cause you to slow down, wasting your time and potentially stopping you from doing time-sensitive tasks

## Items

- **Boba:** because yum. Can be used to befriend *Edna.*  
- **Coffee:** temporary speed boost. *Jerry* becomes more sociable after drinking this (he takes 30 seconds to do so)  
- **Backpack:** lets you take more items and slightly decreases weight penalty  
- **Radio:** plays music of course :) but also could be used for an Easter egg?

More planning is needed for this, but I’ll need to shell out the story first

## Story

VERY much subject to change\!

- You work an office job as a lowly office worker  
- Talk with NPCs  
  - Before 30 seconds: Jerry is grumpy, after drinking Coffee, he’s more cheerful  
    - In starting location to make things trickier  
- *Edna* hands you a coffee (prolly far away?), after rewind, give it to Jerry and he’ll be grateful  
- Jerry casually mentions how *Felix* has been acting weird lately  
- You go talk to *Felix* but he fobs you off
